\textbf{Problem:} Evaluate the integral:
\[ \int (4x^3 - 6x + 2) \, dx \]

\textbf{Solution:}
Using the Power Rule \( \int x^n \, dx = \frac{x^{n+1}}{n+1} \):
\[
\begin{aligned}
\int (4x^3 - 6x + 2) \, dx &= 4\frac{x^4}{4} - 6\frac{x^2}{2} + 2x + C \\
&= x^4 - 3x^2 + 2x + C
\end{aligned}
\]
